A vintage 1960s travel poster aesthetic showing a stylized globe with glowing pin-drop markers scattered across continents, connected by elegant curved lines suggesting data paths. The color palette features warm oranges, teals, and cream. In the foreground, an old brass compass sits beside a retro computer terminal with a curved CRT screen displaying a simple world map. The overall composition suggests the marriage of old-world exploration with digital discovery, rendered with mid-century modern graphic design sensibilities and subtle paper texture throughout.
